  <cite><strong>Kev</strong> </cite> said 1 day later:<br />
  <p>Jorge: Migrations can do integrity constraints. If you look at the <a href="http://api.rubyonrails.org/classes/ActiveRecord/ConnectionAdapters/TableDefinition.html#M000546">column method api</a>  it gives you options for limit (max length), default values and null/not null constraints. I don&#8217;t believe migrations handles anything more complex than that. Really, more complex things are usually reserved for validations in rails anyway</p>
